stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> Eligible: submission ingested<br/>(SubmissionStatus.ELIGIBLE)
    Eligible --> Waiting: registered on chain,<br/>not yet king/challenger

    Waiting --> PoolOne: duel-resolver opens challenge<br/>challenges.status = POOL_ONE (1)

    state "POOL_ONE (best-of N)" as PoolOne
    state "POOL_TWO (best-of N)" as PoolTwo

    PoolOne --> PoolTwo: challenger unbeatable<br/>AdvancePool → status = POOL_TWO (2)<br/>duel_resolutions: CHALLENGER_WON
    PoolOne --> Closed_KingDefends: king cannot be caught<br/>CloseChallenge → CLOSED (0)<br/>duel_resolutions: KING_WON
    PoolOne --> Closed_Dereg: challenger deregistered<br/>CLOSED (0) · CHALLENGER_DEREGISTERED

    PoolTwo --> Crowned: challenger unbeatable<br/>Promote → CLOSED (0) + insert kings row<br/>duel_resolutions: CHALLENGER_WON
    PoolTwo --> Closed_KingDefends: king cannot be caught<br/>CLOSED (0) · KING_WON
    PoolTwo --> Closed_Dereg: challenger deregistered<br/>CLOSED (0) · CHALLENGER_DEREGISTERED

    state "New King crowned" as Crowned
    state "Challenge CLOSED — king defends" as Closed_KingDefends
    state "Challenge CLOSED — forfeit" as Closed_Dereg

    Crowned --> [*]
    Closed_KingDefends --> [*]
    Closed_Dereg --> [*]

    note right of PoolOne
        Win rule (challenger perspective):
        wins > losses + win_margin
        Decided early when the result is
        mathematically locked in.
    end note
